This paper proposes a new type of normalizing flow model that can efficiently transform any continuous random vector into a Gaussian one. The paper focuses on the expressivity and efficiency of the proposed model and demonstrates its performance on several tabular datasets. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
